    "text": "Worth training, but keep it genuinely easy. Recovery at 48% with your HRV at 48 ms — well under your baseline of about 58 ms — plus yesterday's 88-minute session says your body is still paying for recent work. Feeling flat in that picture is ordinary training fatigue, not a warning sign. Today I'd do easy zone-two movement or mobility, nothing that leaves you breathing hard, and protect sleep tonight: last night's 7.3 hours was fine, but you'll benefit from more while the numbers rebound. Expect the flatness to lift as they do. For the boundary: tiredness that tracks with hard training and improves with an easy day is benign, whereas fatigue paired with fever, sore throat, or a racing heart at rest points to illness and a genuine rest day. Nothing in your data or what you've described suggests the latter.",
